 United Kingdom":"Bradford-on-Avon, Wiltshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","East Hoathly, Wealden, East Sussex, England":"East Hoathly, Sussex, England","Smisby, Derbyshire, England":"Smisby, Derbyshire, England","Bradford-on-Avon, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bradford-on-Avon, Wiltshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1326–":"1326–Deceased","1326–Female":"1326–Deceased","1320–1352":"1320–1352","1340–1400":"1340–1400","1349–Female":"1349–Deceased","1352–1430":"1352–1430","1300–1361":"1300–1361","1300–1359":"1300–1359","1349":"1349","1326":"1326","16 JUN 1349":"16 June 1349","1359":"1359","1400":"1400","1300":"1300","1430":"1430","1320":"1320","1352":"1352","1340":"1340","1361":"1361","Cir 1340":"1340","Bradford-on-Avon, Wiltshire district, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bradford-on-Avon, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom","East Hoathly, Wealden, East Sussex, England":"East Hoathly, Sussex, England","Smisby, Derbyshire, England":"Smisby, Derbyshire, England","Bradford-on-Avon, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bradford-on-Avon, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"la","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Vietnamese Hung, Cuong, Anh, Thanh, Ha, Hoang, Tuan, Chau, Hao, Hien, Hoa, Hue, Nam, Phong, Sinh, Tuong, Min, Tam, Tanh, Thai, Tham, Tinh, Yeong.  Chinese Hong, Hang, Sang, Tong, Chan, Chi, Hwa Ja, Hyung, Kam, Ki Bong, Kin, Man.","Vietnamese: from the Chinese surname 羅, see   Luo   1.","Vietnamese (<b>Lã</b>): from the Chinese surname 呂, see   Lu   6 and 3 below."],"variants":[{"name":"Luo","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Wei, Jian, Yi, Ping, Yong, Zhen, Feng, Hong, Ming, Jin, Bin, Chen, Hai, Lan, Min, Huan, Hung, Shen, Tian.","Chinese:","Mandarin form of the surname 羅, meaning ‘net for catching birds’ or ‘to collect’ in Chinese: (i) from Luo (羅), the name of an ancient state (located in present-day Hubei province). After it was annexed by the state of Chu during the early Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ), people from the state migrated southwards and adopted Luo (羅) as their surname. (ii) from the Po Duo Luo (破多羅) and Chi Luo (叱羅) families from the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China, who changed their original surnames to 羅 during the Northern Wei dynasty (386–534  AD ). (iii) from the personal name Hu Se Luo (斛瑟羅), leader of an ancient Turkic tribe who are believed to have migrated to China during the Tang dynasty (618–907  AD ). His descendants inherited his name Hu Se Luo (斛瑟羅) as their surname and shortened it to 羅 during the Northern Wei dynasty (386–534  AD ). (iv) from the name of one of the seven families from the Bandun Man, an ethnic group residing in ancient southwestern China (located mainly in present-day Sichuan province)."]}]},{"name":"Salle","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Jacques, Pierre.","French: topographic name or a metonymic occupational name for someone who lived or worked at a manor house, from Old French <i>salle</i> ‘large room, hall’. Compare   Desalle   and   Lasalle  .","French (<b>Sallé</b>): from Old French <i>salé</i> ‘salty, salted’, hence a metonymic occupational name for someone who dealt with salt meat or salt fish, or perhaps, in a figurative sense, a nickname for a witty or mordant person. Compare   Sallee   and   Salley  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Desalle","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Antonio, Marco, Reno.","Americanized form (also <b>De Salle</b>) of Italian   Di Salle  .","French: shortened form of <b>Delasalle</b>, a variant, with fused preposition <i>de</i> and definite article <i>la</i> ‘from the’, of   Salle   1 ‘large room, hall’."]},{"name":"Sallee","meanings":["French (<b>Sallée</b>): variant of <b>Sallé</b> ‘salted, salty’ (see   Salle  ).","History: This surname is listed in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors."]},{"name":"Salles","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Carlos, Luiz, Ricardo, Ana, Armenia, Ernesto, Fabio, Francisco, Gustavo, Jaime, Luzia, Manuel.  French Andre, Emile, Jean-Luc.","French: variant of   Salle   1.","French: habitational name from (Les) Salles, the name of several places in various parts of France."]}]},{"name":"Edith","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old English female personal name derived from <i>ēad</i> ‘prosperity, riches’ + <i>gӯð</i> ‘strife’. This was borne by a daughter (  961–984 ) of Edgar the Peaceful. (She was named in accordance with the common Old English practice of repeating name elements within a family.) She spent her short life in a convent, and is regarded as a saint."],"variants":[{"name":"Edyth","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Edith ."]},{"name":"Edythe","meanings":["From an Old English female personal name derived from <i>ēad</i> ‘prosperity, riches’ + <i>gӯð</i> ‘strife’. This was borne by a daughter (  961–984 ) of Edgar the Peaceful. (She was named in accordance with the common Old English practice of repeating name elements within a family.) She spent her short life in a convent, and is regarded as a saint."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Lady Edith de la Salle was born in 1326, in Bradford-on-Avon, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, John Sale, was 26 and her mother, Ann Holmes, was 26. She married Thomas Halle II. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"1326–":"1326–Surnud","1326–Female":"1326–Surnud","1320–1352":"1320–1352","1340–1400":"1340–1400","1349–Female":"1349–Surnud","1352–1430":"1352–1430","1300–1361":"1300–1361","1300–1359":"1300–1359","1349":"1349","1326":"1326","16 JUN 1349":"16. juuni 1349","1359":"1359","1400":"1400","1300":"1300","1430":"1430","1320":"1320","1352":"1352","1340":"1340","1361":"1361","Cir 1340":"1340","Bradford-on-Avon, Wiltshire district, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bradford-on-Avon, Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","East Hoathly, Wealden, East Sussex, England":"East Hoathly, Sussex, England","Smisby, Derbyshire, England":"Smisby, Derbyshire, England","Bradford-on-Avon, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bradford-on-Avon, Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1326–":"1326–Kuollut","1326–Female":"1326–Kuollut","1320–1352":"1320–1352","1340–1400":"1340–1400","1349–Female":"1349–Kuollut","1352–1430":"1352–1430","1300–1361":"1300–1361","1300–1359":"1300–1359","1349":"1349","1326":"1326","16 JUN 1349":"16. kesäkuuta 1349","1359":"1359","1400":"1400","1300":"1300","1430":"1430","1320":"1320","1352":"1352","1340":"1340","1361":"1361","Cir 1340":"1340","Bradford-on-Avon, Wiltshire district, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bradford-on-Avon, Wiltshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","East Hoathly, Wealden, East Sussex, England":"East Hoathly, Sussex, England","Smisby, Derbyshire, England":"Smisby, Derbyshire, England","Bradford-on-Avon, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bradford-on-Avon, Wiltshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1326–":"1326–Décédée","1326–Female":